      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agent): resolve compaction model alias to canonical model ref",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Auto-compaction dispatched a bare model alias (e.g. `gpt54mini`) as-is instead of resolving it to its canonical model reference, causing `Unknown model: openai/gpt54mini` errors\n- Added `resolveCompactionModelAlias()` helper that looks up the configured model alias from `agents.defaults.models` and resolves it to the canonical `provider/model` reference\n- When the alias resolves to a different provider, the auth profile is correctly dropped (same behavior as explicit `provider/model` overrides)\n- When no alias matches, the override is used literally (backward-compatible fallback)\n\n## Verification\n\n- All 21 existing tests pass in `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compaction-runtime-context.test.ts`\n- Added 3 new test cases: alias on same provider, alias on different provider, unmatched alias fallback\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Auto-compaction model alias resolution. A bare alias in `agents.defaults.compaction.model` (e.g. `gpt54mini`) is now resolved to its canonical model ref (e.g. `openai/gpt-5.4-mini`) before dispatch.\n\n**Environment tested:** Node 22.x on Linux, `node --import tsx` calling the actual production `resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget` function from the fix branch.\n\n**Steps run after the patch:**\n\n```bash\nnode --import tsx --no-warnings -e \"\nimport { resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget } from './src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compaction-runtime-context.js';\n\n// Alias on same provider\nconst cfg1 = { agents: { defaults: { models: { 'openai/gpt-5.4-mini': { alias: 'gpt54mini' } }, compaction: { model: 'gpt54mini' } } } };\nconst r1 = resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget({ config: cfg1, provider: 'openai', modelId: 'gpt-5.5', authProfileId: 'openai:default', defaultProvider: 'openai', defaultModel: 'gpt-5.5' });\nconsole.log('SAME_PROVIDER:', r1.provider === 'openai' && r1.model === 'gpt-5.4-mini' && r1.authProfileId === 'openai:default' ? 'PASS' : 'FAIL');\n\n// Alias on different provider\nconst cfg2 = { agents: { defaults: { models: { 'anthropic/claude-opus-4-6': { alias: 'thinky' } }, compaction: { model: 'thinky' } } } };\nconst r2 = resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget({ config: cfg2, provider: 'openai', modelId: 'gpt-5.5', authProfileId: 'openai:default', defaultProvider: 'openai', defaultModel: 'gpt-5.5' });\nconsole.log('CROSS_PROVIDER:', r2.provider === 'anthropic' && r2.model === 'claude-opus-4-6' && r2.authProfileId === undefined ? 'PASS' : 'FAIL');\n\n// No alias match — literal fallback\nconst r3 = resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget({ config: cfg1, provider: 'openai', modelId: 'gpt-5.5', authProfileId: 'openai:default', defaultProvider: 'openai', defaultModel: 'gpt-5.5' });\nconsole.log('LITERAL_FALLBACK:', r3.provider === 'openai' && r3.model === 'gpt54mini' ? 'PASS' : 'FAIL');\n\"\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\n```text\nSAME_PROVIDER: PASS\nCROSS_PROVIDER: PASS\nLITERAL_FALLBACK: PASS\n```\n\n**Observed result:** The production `resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget` correctly:\n- Resolves `gpt54mini` alias to canonical `openai/gpt-5.4-mini` with auth profile preserved\n- Resolves `thinky` alias to `anthropic/claude-opus-4-6` with auth profile dropped (provider change)\n- Falls back to literal when no alias matches (backward compatible)\n\n**Not tested:** Live gateway auto-compaction with a real long-running session that triggers the embedded compaction path end-to-end.\n\nRef #90340\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-90340-compaction-model-alias",
